sql:
SELECT residue_id 
FROM residue_surface_accessibility 
WHERE accessibility_score = (SELECT MAX(accessibility_score) FROM residue_surface_accessibility);

SELECT accessibility_score 
FROM residue_surface_accessibility 
WHERE residue_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT protein_id) 
FROM protein_versions 
WHERE version_number = 2;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM residue_comments
WHERE comment_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Protein collectors refer to the users in the database; 
The number of proteins they have gathered refers to the count of proteins accessed by each user; 
The term "protein collectors" is used metaphorically to refer to users who have accessed proteins.

